xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1862</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">hodge-theory-ii-4.2.6-footnote-1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-4.2.6-footnote-1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Footnote</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>1</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-ii-4.2</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> be a smooth connected scheme.
    A <fr:em>family of Hodge structures</fr:em> on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is a continuous family <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> of Hodge structures on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> that satisfies the following conditions:

    
 <html:ol
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(a) &quot;">
        The Hodge filtration on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(H_\mathbb {C})_s]]></fr:tex> varies holomorphically with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex>, i.e. it corresponds to a filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H_\mathcal {O}=H_\mathbb {Z}\otimes \mathcal {O}]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>

      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(b) &quot;">
        The covariant derivative <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\nabla ]]></fr:tex> satisfies <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\nabla  F^p\subset \Omega _S^1\otimes  F^{p-1}]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> be the category of such continuous families of Hodge <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex>-structures on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> that underlie a family of Hodge structures and whose homogeneous direct factors are polarisable.
    It is clear that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {C}]]></fr:tex> satisfies <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2.1"
href="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2.1.xml"
taxon="Condition"
number="4.2.2.1" />, <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2.2"
href="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2.2.xml"
taxon="Condition"
number="4.2.2.2" />, and <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2.3"
href="hodge-theory-ii-4.2.2.3.xml"
taxon="Condition"
number="4.2.2.3" />.
    We can deduce from results of W. Schmid (August 1970, unpublished) and P.A. Griffiths [<fr:link
type="local"
